Recodes needed

All of these variables present themselves as numeric variables, but some are clearly categorical. Female is 0 or 1. The R tradition would not have us treat that as a number, but rather it should be a factor variable. Same with minority. Lets make factor versions of them. So we need to make them into factor variables.

I’ll take some liberty here and rename in a way that is, in my opinion, more correct. The variable is “gender” (not female), which takes values Male and Female.

hsb$gender <- factor(hsb$female, levels= c(0, 1), labels = c("Male", "Female"))
hsb$ethnicity <- factor(hsb$minority, levels = c(0, 1), labels = c("White", "Non-white"))
hsb$sector <- factor(hsb$sector, levels = c(0, 1), labels = c("Public", "Catholic"))

Double-check the recoding

with(hsb, table(gender, female))
##         female
## gender      0    1
##   Male   3390    0
##   Female    0 3795
with(hsb, table(ethnicity, minority))
##            minority
## ethnicity      0    1
##   White     5211    0
##   Non-white    0 1974

If you are comfortable with those recodes, you can move on. I’m going to remove the original variables, just to show I can.

hsb$female <- NULL
hsb$minority <- NULL

If we were going to do any “multi-level” regressions, we would need the school variable as a factor, not as an integer. I’m going to make that one into a factor called schoolidf

hsb$schoolidf <- as.factor(hsb$schoolid)

Plainly, there are other variables in the collection that need the same treatment, but I’m not bothering with them now.

xyplot(mathach ~ ses | schoolidf, data = hsb2,

What best way to get plot for each school.

My plotSlopes approach is not what they want

m1 <- lm(mathach ~ ses * schoolidf, data = hsb2)
plotSlopes(m1, plotx = "ses", modx = "schoolidf", xlim = c(-2, 2),
           ylim = c(-10, 30))

xyplot(mathach ~ ses | schoolidf, data = hsb2, type = c("p", "r"))

library(ggplot2)
theme_set(theme_bw())
ggplot(data = hsb2, aes(x=ses, y=mathach)) + geom_point(alpha=0.5) +
    geom_line(data = m0.pom$ses) +
    geom_ribbon(data = m0.pom$ses, aes(ymin = lwr, ymax = upr), fill = "pink", alpha = 0.5)

ggplot(data = hsb2, aes(x=ses, y=mathach)) + geom_point(alpha=0.5) +
    geom_line(data = m0.pom$ses) +
    geom_ribbon(data = m0.pom$ses, aes(ymin = lwr, ymax = upr), fill = "pink", alpha = 0.5) +
    geom_smooth(method="lm", fill = NA) + 
    facet_wrap(~ schoolidf)

1.1.8 Regression with school as a factor

Test the school coefficients, jointly

anova(m0, m2)
## Analysis of Variance Table
